      • DEFAULT_WINDOW_MONITOR_INTERVAL

        public static final long DEFAULT_WINDOW_MONITOR_INTERVAL
        Default amount of time (milliseconds) between executions of monitoring the window for requests that expire. It's recommended that this generally either matches or is half the value of requestExpiryTimeout. Therefore, at worst a request would could take up 1.5X the requestExpiryTimeout to clear out (disabled [-1]).
        See Also:

      • DEFAULT_RESPONSE_TIMEOUT

        public static final long DEFAULT_RESPONSE_TIMEOUT
        Set the maximum amount of time (in milliseconds) to wait until a valid response is received when a "submit" request is synchronously sends to the remote endpoint. The timeout value includes both waiting for a "window" slot, the time it takes to transmit the actual bytes on the socket, and for the remote endpoint to send a response back (5000 ms).
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • DEFAULT_UNBIND_TIMEOUT

        public static final long DEFAULT_UNBIND_TIMEOUT
        Set the maximum amount of time (in milliseconds) to wait until the session is unbounded, waiting up to a specified period of milliseconds for an unbind response from the remote endpoint. Regardless of whether a proper unbind response was received, the socket/channel is closed (5000 ms).

      • DEFAULT_LAST_INTERACTION_EXPIRATION_DELAY

        public static final long DEFAULT_LAST_INTERACTION_EXPIRATION_DELAY
        Default expiration delay (30000 ms). To check if the session is still alive, an EnquireLink request is sent. The request is sent just before sending the message. This is the time (in milliseconds) to wait before considering last EnquireLink response as expired (need to send a new EnquireLink request to check if session is still alive). This is needed to prevent sending EnquireLink request every time a message has to be sent. Instead it considers that the time elapsed between now and the last EnquireLink response (or the last sent message) is not enough so a new EnquireLink is not necessary to check if session is still alive. Set to 0 to always check session before sending message.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • DEFAULT_ENQUIRE_LINK_REUSE_RESPONSE_TIMEOUT

        public static final long DEFAULT_ENQUIRE_LINK_REUSE_RESPONSE_TIMEOUT
        Default response timeout to an EnquireLink request (10000 ms). To check if the session is still alive, an EnquireLink request is sent. This request may fail since the session may be killed by the server. The timeout ensures that the client doesn't wait too long for a response that may never come. The maximum amount of time (in milliseconds) to wait for receiving a response from the server to an EnquireLink request.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • DEFAULT_KEEP_ALIVE_MAX_CONSECUTIVE_TIMEOUTS

        public static final Integer DEFAULT_KEEP_ALIVE_MAX_CONSECUTIVE_TIMEOUTS
        Default number of consecutive EnquireLink requests that end in a timeout.
